# Adapted from the Standard Tamil apertium-tam available at https://github.com/apertium/apertium-tam.git, by Maathavan Nithiyananthan <maathumaathavan@gmail.com>
# Morphological Transducer for Jaffna Tamil

# Part of speech categories
# <prn>    # Pronoun
# <n>      # Noun
# <v>      # Verb
# <adj>    # Adjective
# <comp>   # Comparative
# <post>   # Postposition
# <caus>   # Causative particles
# <num>    # Numeral

# <sent>   # Sentence-ending punctuation
# <guio>   # Hyphen
# <cm>     # Comma
# <apos>   # Apostrophe
# <quot>   # Quotation mark
# <lquot>  # Left quotation mark
# <rquot>  # Right quotation mark
# <lpar>   # Left parenthesis
# <rpar>   # Right parenthesis

# Number morphology
# <sg>     # Singular
# <pl>     # Plural
# <epl>    # Epicene Plural

# Other symbols
# >        # Morpheme boundary

###############################################################################
###                       M O R P H O T A C T I C S                         ###
###############################################################################

################################     PATTERNS     ################################
PATTERNS
# Pronouns
## Location necessary
Location(1)[LOC] PronounStems[LOC,GPro] Number[GPro] Cases[AA] Location(2)[LOC] Interrogative?
Location(1)[LOC] PronounStems[LOC,FPro] Number[FPro] Cases[AA] Location(2)[LOC] Interrogative?
### Honorifics
Location(1)[LOC] PronounStems[LOC,MH] Number[MH] Honorifics[MH] Cases[AA] Location(2)[LOC] Interrogative?
Location(1)[LOC] PronounStems[LOC,FH] Number[FH] Honorifics[FH] Cases[AA] Location(2)[LOC] Interrogative?
Location(1)[LOC] PronounStems[LOC,EHIrr] Number[EHIrr] Honorifics[EHIrr] Cases[AA] Location(2)[LOC] Interrogative?
## Non-location
Location(1)[NOC] PronounStems[NOC,GPro] Number[GPro] Cases[AA] Location(2)[NOC] Interrogative?
### Honorifics
Location(1)[NOC] PronounStems[NOC,PH] Number[PH] Honorifics[PH] Cases[AA] Location(2)[NOC] Interrogative?
Location(1)[NOC] PronounStems[NOC,IH] Number[IH] Honorifics[IH] Cases[AA] Location(2)[NOC] Interrogative?
# Nouns & NP
## Irregulars
Nouns[NN,MNoun] Number[MNoun] Cases[NN]|Emphatic
Nouns[NN,FNoun] Number[FNoun] Cases[NN]|Emphatic
Nouns[TNoun] Number[TNoun] Cases[AA]|Emphatic
Nouns[NN,PRED] Number[Pl1] Cases[NN]|Emphatic Predicative[PRED]?
Nouns[AA,ES] Number[ES] Cases[AA]|Emphatic
Nouns[VIrr,Pl1] Number[Pl1] Cases[VIrr]
## Honorifics
Nouns[AA,H] Number[H] Honorifics[H] Cases[AA]
Nouns[AA,EH] Number[EH] Honorifics[H] Cases[AA]
## Regulars
Nouns[NN,Pl1] Number[Pl1] Cases[NN]|Emphatic
Nouns[AA,Pl1] Number[Pl1] Cases[AA]|Emphatic
Nouns[NN,Pl2] Number[Pl2] Cases[NN]|Emphatic
Nouns[AA,Pl2] Number[Pl2] Cases[AA]|Emphatic
Nouns[NN,Pl3] Number[Pl3] Cases[NN]|Emphatic
Nouns[AA,Pl3] Number[Pl3] Cases[AA]|Emphatic
Nouns[NN,Pl4] Number[Pl4] Cases[NN]|Emphatic
Nouns[AA,Pl4] Number[Pl4] Cases[AA]|Emphatic
Nouns[NN,Pl5] Number[Pl5] Cases[NN]|Emphatic
Nouns[AA,Pl5] Number[Pl5] Cases[AA]|Emphatic
Nouns[NN,Pl6] Number[Pl6] Cases[NN]|Emphatic
Nouns[AA,Pl6] Number[Pl6] Cases[AA]|Emphatic
Nouns[NN,Pl7] Number[Pl7] Cases[NN]|Emphatic
Nouns[AA,Pl7] Number[Pl7] Cases[AA]|Emphatic
Nouns[NN,Pl8] Number[Pl8] Cases[NN]|Emphatic
Nouns[AA,Pl8] Number[Pl8] Cases[AA]|Emphatic
# Verbs
## Transitives
### Infinitives
TransVerbStem [ <v><tv>: ] Infinitives
### Passivisers
TransVerbStem[PASSIVE] [ <v><tv>: ] Voice[PASSIVE]
TransVerbStem [ <v><tv>: ] Voice[-PASSIVE]
### Causativisers
TransVerbStem[Class1a] [ <v><tv>: ] Causativiser[Class1a]
TransVerbStem[Class3] [ <v><tv>: ] Causativiser[Class3]
TransVerbStem[Class4] [ <v><tv>: ] Causativiser[Class4]
TransVerbStem[Class6] [ <v><tv>: ] Causativiser[Class6]
TransVerbStem[Class7] [ <v><tv>: ] Causativiser[Class7]
TransVerbStem[WEAKDOUBCAUS] [ <v><tv>: ] Causativiser[WEAKDOUBCAUS]
TransVerbStem[CAUSIRR2] [ <v><tv>: ] Causativiser[CAUSIRR2]
## Intransitives
### Infinitives
IntraVerbStem [ <v><iv>: ] Infinitives
### Passivisers
IntraVerbStem[PASSIVE] [ <v><iv>: ] Voice[PASSIVE]
### Causativisers
IntraVerbStem[INTRACAUS] [ <v><iv>: ] Causativiser[INTRACAUS]
IntraVerbStem[CAUSIRR1] [ <v><iv>: ] Causativiser[CAUSIRR1]
IntraVerbStem[STRONGDOUBCAUS] [ <v><iv>: ] Causativiser[STRONGDOUBCAUS]
# Others
Adjectives [ <adj>: ] Predicative[APRED]? Honorifics[H]?
Comparatives [ <post><comp>: ]
PostPositions [ <post>: ]
CausativePart [ <caus>: ]
Numbers
Symbol
Fraction
Measure
Punctuation

################################     SUFFIXOLOGY     ################################
########################### GENERAL
################## HONORIFICS
LEXICON Honorifics
## 'kaaran' is usually added for professions (female eq. 'kaari')
## this is changed to 'kaarar' in both male and female to denote honor
## this is similar to the general honorific, '-r', which changes (mainly male) '-n' ending nouns
# General honorific
<hon>:>{R}{Pul}[H]                                    # 'r'   honorific
# Epicene plural (implied honorific)
<hon>:>{R}{Pul}[EH]                                   # 'r'   honorific
# For pronouns (applied to p2,p3)
## p2
<ihon>:>{R}{Pul}[IH]                                  # 'r'   intermediate honorific
<hon>:>{K}ள{Pul}[PH]                                 # 'kal' plural honorific
## p3
<hon>:>{R}{Pul}[MH]                                   # 'r'   male honorific
<hon>:>{AA}[FH]                                       # 'aa'  female honorific
<hon>:>{AI}[EHIrr]                                    # 'ai'  irregular epicene plural honorific
# add more honorifics

################## NUMBER
LEXICON Number
# ORUMAI: Singular Class: 0
# 0: a. Foodstuffs         [FNoun]                               (Always singular)
##   b. Toponyms           [TNoun]                               (Always singular)
##   c. Pronouns           [GPro,FPro]                           (Singular form)
##   d. Epicenes           [ES]                                  (Dont have regular plural)
##   e. Regular Nouns      [Pl1,Pl2,Pl3,Pl4,Pl5,Pl6,Pl7,Pl8]     (Singular form)
##   f. Honorifics         [IH,H,MH,FH,PH]                       (Forced singular for honorifics 'null')
##   g. Mass Nouns         [MNoun]                               (Uncountable)
<sg>:[FNoun,TNoun,GPro,FPro]                  # null  singular
<sg>:[ES,Pl1,Pl2,Pl3,Pl4,Pl5,Pl6,Pl7,Pl8]     # null  singular
<sg>:[IH,H,FH,MH,PH]                          # null  singular
<unc>:[MNoun]                                 # null  uncountable

# PANMAI: Plural Classes: 1 through 8
# 1/2: Epicene Plural (Unisex)
# Ungendered forced plural used for groups of people, honorific implied [EH,EHIrr]
<epl>:[EH,EHIrr]
###### GENERAL CLASSES
# 1: Common Plural (Inanimate and Animate)
# This plural also applies to pronouns generally [GPro]
<pl>:>{K}ள{Pul}[Pl1,GPro]           # 'kal'

# 2: Plurals of feminine Proper Nouns, people related to locations (Animate)
# This plural also applies to female pronouns [FPro]
<pl>:>{A}வ{AI}[Pl2,FPro]            # 'avay'

# 3: Variation of Common Plural (Inanimate and Animate)
<pl>:>{A}ள{Pul}[Pl3]                # 'al'

###### AHTHINAI 'irrational beings and inanimate objects' - Low Class (NON-GENDERED)
# 4: Non humans (Inanimate and Irrational Animates)
<pl>:>{U}கள{Pul}[Pl4]              # 'ukal'
## Special form
<pl>:>{U}ள{Pul}[Pl4]                # 'ul'      Dir/LR

###### UYARTHINAI 'rational beings' - High Class(es) (GENDERED)
# 5: Professional terms and loanwords (Animates)
<pl>:>ம{AA}ர{Pul}[Pl5]              # 'maar'

# 6: Combination of 2 and 5 (Animates) (RELATIONS)
<pl>:>ம{AA}ர{Pul}[Pl6]              # 'maar'
<pl>:>{A}வ{AI}[Pl6]                 # 'avay'    Dir/LR

# 7: Combination of 2, 3 and 5 (Animates only) (Mainly FEMALES)
<pl>:>{A}ள{Pul}[Pl7]                # 'al'
<pl>:>ம{AA}ர{Pul}[Pl7]              # 'maar'    Dir/LR
<pl>:>{A}வ{AI}[Pl7]                 # 'avay'     Dir/LR

# 8: -N ending nouns (Animates) (MALES)
<pl>:>{R}{Pul}[Pl8]                  # 'r'

################## CASES
LEXICON Cases
<nom>:[AA,NN]                                    # null
<acc>:>{AI}[AA]                                  # 'ay'
<int>:>{AA}லை[AA,NN]                           # 'aalay~ai'
<dat>:>{U}க்கு[AA,NN]                            # 'ukku'
<dat>:>{AI}[VIrr]                                # 'ay'             (irregular dative for 'veetu')    Dir/LR
<com>:>{OO}டை[AA,NN]                           # 'ootay~ai'
<loc>:>{I}லை[AA,NN]                            # 'ilay~ai'
<refr>:>{Irefr}ட்டை[AA]                         # 'ittay~ai'
<gen>:>{I}{N}{Pul}{R}{AI}[AA,NN]                 # 'inray~ai'
<gen>:[AA,NN]                                    # null             (irregular genitive)              Dir/LR
<abl>:>{I}ட்டை\ இருந்து[AA,NN]                 # 'ittay~ai iruntu'
<abl>:>{I}லை\ இருந்து[AA,NN]                  # 'ilay~ai iruntu'                                    Dir/LR
<ben>:>{AA}க[AA,NN]                             # 'aaka'
# fix ask about ai

################## INTERROGATIVE
LEXICON Interrogative
<qst>:{AA}              # 'aa'
# fix add for verbs after tenses and such

########################### NOUNS
################## EMPHATIC
LEXICON Emphatic
<emph>:>{AI}                                     # 'ay'

################## PREDICATIVE
LEXICON Predicative
<pred>:[PRED]                                    # null        built-in for <nq>
# Pronominalizing predicatives (GENDERED)
<pron><pred><nt>:>{C}{U}[APRED]                  # 'cu'        neuter (adjectives)  
<pron><pred><f>:>வ{PLR}{Pul}[APRED]             # 'val'       female (adjectives)  
<pron><pred><m>:>வ{NR}{Pul}[APRED]              # 'val'       male (adjectives)  

########################### VERBS
################## VOICE
LEXICON Voice
<actv>:
<pasv>:>ப்பட்டு                        # 'ppattu'
<pasv>:>{U}ண்டு[PASSIVE]              # 'untu'      eat

################## CAUSATIVE
LEXICON Causativiser
# Weak verb causitive marker
<caus>:>வி[Class1a,Class3,Class4,INTRACAUS]      # 'vi'

# Strong verb causitive marker
<caus>:>ப்பி[Class6,Class7]                       # 'ppi'

# Irregular causitive markers
<caus>:>த்து[CAUSIRR1]                            # 'ththu'
<caus>:>{II}[CAUSIRR2]                            # 'ii'

# Irregular double causitive marker
<caus><caus>:விப்பி[WEAKDOUBCAUS]                 # 'vippi'
<caus><caus>:த்துவி[STRONGDOUBCAUS]               # 'ththuvi'

################## INFINITIVE
LEXICON Infinitives
<inf>:>{A}                                        # 'a'           
# fix based on classes

########################### PRONOUN LOCATION
LEXICON Location(2)
# No location prefix for p1,p2
:[NOC]                   :[NOC]
# Mandatory prefix for p3
:இ>[LOC]           <prx>:[LOC]
:உ>[LOC]           <med>:[LOC]
:அ>[LOC]           <dst>:[LOC]

################################     PARTICLES     ################################
LEXICON CausativePart
வை:வைக்க                            # 'vaykka'
வை:வச்சு                              # 'vaccu'            Dir/LR
செய்:செய்த                            # 'ceitha'          Dir/LR
பண்ணு:பண்ணினா                    # 'panninaa'         Dir/LR
கொள்:கொண்டு                       # 'kontu'            Dir/LR
பிடி:பிடிச்சு                             # 'piticcu'          Dir/LR

###############################################################################
###                          L E X I C O N                                  ###
###############################################################################
################################     PRONOUN STEMS     ################################
LEXICON PronounStems
நான்<prn><p1>:நா{N}{Pul}[NOC,GPro]           # 'naan'             I
நீ<prn><p2>:ந{II}{AN}[NOC,GPro,PH,IH]          # 'nee'             you
வன்<prn><p3><m>:வ>{NR}{Pul}[LOC,GPro,MH]     # '-van'            -he
வள்<prn><p3><f>:வ>{PL}{Pul}[LOC,FPro,FH]     # '-val'            -she
வ<prn><p3>:வ[LOC,EHIrr]                      # '-va'            -they-
து<prn><p3><nt>:த{U}[LOC,GPro]                # '-tu'            -they

################################     NOUNS & NP     ################################
LEXICON Nouns
#####
# UYARTHINAI Grouped into FEMALE, MALE and UNISEX
# FEMALE and MALE further grouped into Classes I - IV
# 0th Class contains words with no gendered equivalent or irregulars
#####
# MALE I: -'an', II: -'aan', III: -'van', IV: communal words
# FEMALE I(a): -'al', (b): -'i', (c): -'aththi', (d): -'cci',
## II(a): -'aal', II(b): -'aaththi', II(c): -'aatti'
## III: -'ththi', IV: communal words  
##################### ANIMATE
# Class 1
## UNGENDERED (AHTHINAI Animate)
மாட்டு<n><aa>:மாட்ட{U}[AA,Pl1]                                   # 'maattu'          cow
ஆடு<n><aa>:ஆட{U}[AA,Pl1]                                       # 'aatu'            goat
## FEMALE
### 0
பெண்<n><f><aa>:பெ{N}{Pul}[AA,Pl1]                              # 'pen'             female
## MALE
### 0
ஆண்<n><m><aa>:ஆ{N}{Pul}[AA,Pl1]                               # 'aan'              male
### I
வேலைக்காரன்<n><m><aa>:வேலை>க்காரன{Pul}[AA,Pl1]           # 'veelaykkaaran'   male servant
பைடியன்<n><m><aa>:பைடிய{N}{Pul}[AA,Pl1]                      # 'petiyan'          boy
### IV
பண்டாரம்<n><m><aa>:பண்டார{M}{Pul}[AA,Pl1]                    # 'pantaaram'       male from pantaaram comm.
பண்டாரி<n><m><aa>:பண்டார{I}[AA,Pl1]                          # 'pantaari'        male from pantaaram comm.          Dir/LR

# Class 2
## FEMALE
### II(a)
தீவாள்<n><f><aa>:தீவாள{Pul}[AA,Pl2]                             # 'theevaal'       lady from an island
பன்னாலயாள்<n><f><aa>:பன்னாலயாள{Pul}[AA,Pl2]              # 'pannaalayaal'   lady from pannaalai
கட்டுவனாள்<n><f><aa>:கட்டுவனாள{Pul}[AA,Pl2]                 # 'kattuvanaal'    lady from kattuvan
பிரத்தியாள்<n><f><aa>:பிரத்தியாள{Pul}[AA,Pl2]                   # 'piraththiyaal'  lady from a different place

## (0) Proper Nouns
பொன்னம்பலம்<np><m><aa>:பொன்னம்பல{M}{Pul}[AA,Pl2]        # 'Ponnambalam'
அருள்<np><m><aa>:அருள{Pul}[AA,Pl2]                             # 'Arul'
### -N or -R ending irregulars
முருகன்<np><m><aa>:முருக{NP}{Pul}[AA,Pl2]                       # 'Murugan'
கண்ணன்<np><m><aa>:கண்ண{NP}{Pul}[AA,Pl2]                   # 'Kannan'

# Class 3
## UNISEX
பிள்ளை<n><mf><aa>:பிள்ள{AI}[AA,Pl3]                            # 'pillay'          child
## FEMALE
### 0
பெட்டை<n><f><aa>:பெட்ட{AI}[AA,Pl3]                            # 'pettay'          girl
### I(b)
மீன்காரி<n><f><aa>:மீன்>கார{I}[AA,Pl3]                          # 'meenkaari'       fisherwoman
வேலைக்காரி<n><f><aa>:வேலை>க்கார{I}[AA,Pl3]                # 'veelaykkaari'    female servant

# Class 4
## UNGENDERED (AHTHINAI Animate)
மான்<n><aa>:மா{N}{Pul}[AA,Pl4]                                 # 'maan'            deer
நுல்லான்<n><aa>:நுள்ளா{N}{Pul}[AA,Pl4]                         # 'nullaan'         small reddish ant

# Class 5
## UNISEX
எஞ்சினியர்<n><mf><aa>:எஞ்சினியர{Pul}[AA,Pl5]                  # 'enciniyar'       engineer
கிளார்க்<n><mf><aa>:கிளார்க்{Pul}[AA,Pl5]                         # 'kilaakku'        clerk
மேனேஜர்<n><mf><aa>:மேனேஜர{Pul}[AA,Pl5]                      # 'maneeccar'       manager
டாக்டர்<n><mf><aa>:டாக்டர{Pul}[AA,Pl5]                           # 'taaktar'         doctor

# Class 6
## FEMALE
### 0 
தோழி<n><f><aa>:தோழ{I}[AA,Pl6]                                # 'thoozhi'         female friend
தங்கச்சி<n><f><aa>:தங்கச்ச{I}[AA,Pl6]                            # 'thankachchi'     younger sister
அம்மா<n><f><aa>:அம்ம{AA}[AA,Pl6]                               # 'amma'            mother
### I(b)
மாமி<n><f><aa>:மாம{I}[AA,Pl6]                                  # 'maami'           aunt
## MALE
### 0
மாமா<n><m><aa>:மாம{AA}[AA,Pl6]                                # 'maamaa'          uncle
அம்மான்<n><m><aa>:அம்மா{N}{Pul}[AA,Pl6]                       # 'ammaan'          uncle                              Dir/LR
மச்சான்<n><m><aa>:மச்சா{N}{Pul}[AA,Pl6]                         # 'maccaan'         male cousin
அய்யர்<n><m><aa>:அய்யர{Pul}[AA,Pl6]                            # 'ayyar'           Hindu priest
ஐயர்<n><m><aa>:ஐயர{Pul}[AA,Pl6]                                # 'aiyar'           Hindu priest                       Dir/LR
அப்பா<n><m><aa>:அப்ப{AA}[AA,Pl6]                               # 'appa'            father
தம்பி<n><m><aa>:தம்ப{I}[AA,Pl6]                                 # 'thambi'          younger brother
### II
கட்டுவனான்<n><m><aa>:கட்டுவனா{N}{Pul}[AA,Pl6]               # 'kattuvanaan'     male from kattuvan
பிரத்தியான்<n><m><aa>:பிரத்தியான{Pul}[AA,Pl6]                 # 'piraththiyaan'   male from a different place
வண்ணான்<n><m><aa>:வண்ணான{Pul}[AA,Pl6]                  # 'vannaan'         washerman
